feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 24, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uzg1665703197654.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzg1665703197654.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzg1665703197654.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uzg1665703197654\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">UROUTER_SET_UST \n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Change or create UST settings for the Uniface Router.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__section_t3k_nv3_nvb\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">operation UROUTER_SET_UST</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">params</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">string</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UST</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"> : IN ; (C20)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">numeric</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Max</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"> : IN ; (I4)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">numeric</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxidle</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"> : IN ; (I4)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">numeric</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxrequests</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">: IN ; (I4)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">string</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Dir</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"> : IN ; (C256)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">string</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Qualifiers</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"> : IN ; (C256)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">endparams</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__section_b3y_nr1_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931139e134\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__ul_pgm_sr1_hwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48062e1_d48063e1_d48064e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UST</var>—Uniface Server Type (UST) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48065e1_d48066e1_d48067e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Max</var>—maximum number of servers allowed </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48068e1_d48069e1_d48070e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxidle</var>—maximum idle time in seconds </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48071e1_d48072e1_d48073e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxrequests</var>—maximum number of requests allowed </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48074e1_d48075e1_d48076e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Dir</var>—working directory for servers started under this UST definition;\n          allowed only for new USTs </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48077e1_d48078e1_d48079e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Qualifiers</var>—optional string of command line switches to use in starting\n          this UST’s servers. Observe the following restrictions: <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__ul_qgm_sr1_hwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48080e1_d48081e1_d48082e1\">If the UST you enter matches a specific or a\n              default UST definition, you may not use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dir</span> and\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/asn</span> switches. Otherwise, these switches and the switches\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dnp</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/shr</span>,\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/su</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">-nosu</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pri</span>, and\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/drv</span> may be used. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48083e1_d48084e1_d48085e1\">You may not use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/max</span>,\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxidle</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxreq</span> switches; use the\n              Maximum parameters instead. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__li_d48086e1_d48087e1_d48088e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/drv</span> switch determines the\n              type of server to be started, for example, ORA for an Oracle database server, FIL for\n              a file server, or S3C for a Uniface Virtual Machine server. For a database server, the\n              database user name and password will be determined by the first client request\n              assigned to the server. <p class=\"p\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__p_d135479e1_d135480e1_d135481e1\">If the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/drv</span> switch is not specified, it defaults to the ANY\n                server.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__section_l2d_tr1_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931139e238\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__p_d134921e1_d134922e1_d134923e1\">If successful, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is set to 0.\n        Otherwise, see the \"Return Codes\" section in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qln1665702528769.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qln1665702528769.html\" title=\"UROUTMON is an internal component that enables you to write your own Uniface Router monitor to access and modify the Uniface Router's parameters and settings.\">UROUTMON</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__section_rc4_xr1_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931139e257\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__p_d135212e1_d135213e1_d135214e1\">Allowed in all Uniface component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__section_zws_yr1_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931139e266\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__p_d135497e1_d135498e1_d135499e1\">The privileged-user operation\n          <span class=\"keyword apiname\">UROUTER_SET_UST</span> changes the settings in the Uniface Router for an\n        existing Uniface Server Type (UST) definition or creates a new one.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzg1665703197654__p_d135500e1_d135501e1_d135502e1\">Only the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Max</var>,\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxidle</var>, <var class=\"keyword varname\">Maxrequests</var> settings may be changed on a\n        UST definition that already exists. For all maximum limits, the value <code class=\"ph codeph\">-2</code>\n        means no change, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">-1</code> means unlimited.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532912\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532912\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UROUTER_SET_UST Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 24, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 UROUTER_SET_UST Change or create UST settings for the Uniface Router. operation UROUTER_SET_UST params string UST : IN ; (C20) numeric Max : IN ; (I4) numeric Maxidle : IN ; (I4) numeric Maxrequests : IN ; (I4) string Dir : IN ; (C256) string Qualifiers : IN ; (C256) endparams Parameters UST —Uniface Server Type (UST) Max —maximum number of servers allowed Maxidle —maximum idle time in seconds Maxrequests —maximum number of requests allowed Dir —working directory for servers started under this UST definition; allowed only for new USTs Qualifiers —optional string of command line switches to use in starting this UST’s servers. Observe the following restrictions: If the UST you enter matches a specific or a default UST definition, you may not use the /dir and /asn switches. Otherwise, these switches and the switches /dnp , /ex , /shr , /su , -nosu , /pri , and /drv may be used. You may not use the /max , /maxidle , and /maxreq switches; use the Maximum parameters instead. The /drv switch determines the type of server to be started, for example, ORA for an Oracle database server, FIL for a file server, or S3C for a Uniface Virtual Machine server. For a database server, the database user name and password will be determined by the first client request assigned to the server. If the /drv switch is not specified, it defaults to the ANY server. Return Values If successful, $status is set to 0. Otherwise, see the \"Return Codes\" section in UROUTMON . Use Allowed in all Uniface component types. Description The privileged-user operation UROUTER_SET_UST changes the settings in the Uniface Router for an existing Uniface Server Type (UST) definition or creates a new one. Only the Max , Maxidle , Maxrequests settings may be changed on a UST definition that already exists. For all maximum limits, the value -2 means no change, and -1 means unlimited. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}